04643nam a22007935i 9789814786560DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20172017si     fo  d z      eng d  a97898147865607 a10.1355/97898147865602doi  a(DE-B1597)522135  a(OCoLC)1096436488  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  asicSG 7aBUS0360502bisacsh1 aNg, Keng Khoon, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aBeneath the Veneer :bThe Political Economy of Housing in Iskandar Malaysia, Johor /cGuanie Lim, Keng Khoon Ng. 1aSingapore : bISEAS Publishing, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (28 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tFOREWORD -- tEXECUTIVE SUMMARY -- tINTRODUCTION -- tOVERVIEW OF HOUSING DEVELOPMENT IN JOHOR -- tISKANDAR MALAYSIA: JOHOR’S LATEST CROWN JEWEL? -- tJOHOR’S HOUSING POLICY: CHANGES AND DEVIATIONS -- tJOHOR’S HOUSING POLICY: CHANGES AND DEVIATIONS -- tCONCLUSION -- tREFERENCES0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe rise of Iskandar Malaysia as a regional hub has profoundly altered the domestic landscape, generating a knock-on effect on Johor's housing development, both economically and politically. Housing policy and development in Johor, as illustrated in the formation of Iskandar Malaysia, is riddled with conflict along two dimensions — bumiputra versus non-bumiputra and federal government versus state government. The first one is entangled with international real estate development and foreign investment, while the latter has more to do with the rise of sub-national autonomy in Johor. Particularly in southern Johor, housing policy has increasingly been influenced by foreign investment through implementations of mega projects (e.g., Forest City). These mega housing projects not only boost the states coffers, but also change the way housing is produced, financed and governed. Given the importance of sub-national governments in many large-scale housing projects in Iskandar Malaysia, the changing political conditions urge us to rethink the long-standing practice of national-centric development policy in Malaysia. Taking housing as a point of departure, the timing is ripe to revisit the role of state government in policy-making and urban governance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHousing development—Malaysia—Johor. 0aHousing policy—Malaysia—Johor. 0aHousing—Economic aspects—Malaysia—Johor. 0aIskandar Malaysia (Johor, Malaysia)—Politics and government. 0aReal Estate Investment. 4aReal Estate Investment. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Investments & Securities / Real Estate.2bisacsh1 aLim, Guanie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066298608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060667640uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981478656040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814786560423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814786560.jpg  a978-3-11-060667-6  ISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066298-6  ISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK